phrases: TS
OP
Agent Nakamura, you still have not given up?
You failed to retrieve the Mark I four months ago, did not you?
The IFO plan has been cancelled.
But our country is under an international embargo
and we are in an explosive situation with both Okinawa and the Allies.
If we acquired a form of absolute defense,
we would have a chance to become the strongest economy in the world!
Listen here, Nakamura.
Japan got this far precisely because we have avoided fishy business like this.
Why stir up unnecessary military tensions and worsen the situation?
The people are allergic to these Scub and trapar stuff.
So you are saying that, no matter what, our budget plan will not be approved by the Ministry of Interior.
Please give it up.
No luck?
They just want their coward's peace until they die.
They do not give a damn about our country's future!
Now we have got no choice but to prove our point
and make them give an ex post facto approval.
I am sending over the data I received from the Fire Crackers.
Are you sure it is okay to trust them?
Are not they considered cyber terrorists?
Should we really interact with them as representatives of a country?
I would say the Fire Crackers are taking pity on Japan,
since we have been ostracized from the rest of the world in terms of information.
Is not this the data the Americans kept refusing to hand over?
How on Earth...
For now, I do not care how they did it.
Our generation needs this...
in order to destroy this country once.
Hey, we have got to train!
Stop fooling around.
But this is training.
Why do not you jump in and join us?
But we really need to have proper training!
Yeah, yeah, I understand you want to get your girlfriend back.
She is not my girlfriend...
Oh?
Are you frustrated?
Ao, you cannot swim?
Or just afraid your worries would pull you down?
Oh, please...
Oh, so you cannot swim?
Then I will not help you if you are about to drown, even if you cry for help.
Of course I know how to swim.
We have got some new intel from a mole inside the Ministry of Defense.
You even have people in the Japanese government?
Results notwithstanding, supposedly they will be conducting simulations of artificial Scub Bursts.
To preserve the power balance of the world,
we absolutely cannot allow Japan, in their misguided state, to get their hands on a plant coral.
And that is where our company's ace, team Pied Piper comes into the picture.
You mean we should secretly retrieve the Quartz?
But it is same order as usual.
Hurry up.
Anyway, I will leave it in your hands.
I will have one of our accomplished employees to brief you on the specifics.
Understood...
Sideseeing!
My mother re-marry in Switzerland.
My Japanese, very good!
Have a tad ov an accent though.
So this is Japan, huh...
Now an Okinawan counts as a foreigner here.
Such a bureaucratic immigration procedure...
It is like we have gone back in time.
And now?
We are taking that.
Heading east.
They call it the Shinkansen.
So Tokyo used to be there a long time ago.
Yeah, the Scub Burst that happened 70 years ago
dealt the final blow to Japan after their defeat in the war,
and caused the reconstructions to be pushed back.
Light emission confirmed.
Water temperature rising.
The damaged Quartz seem to have started fusing.
Great!
The reactivation is successful!
Our country has got a plant coral now.
Reactivation is the first step in the plan.
Huh?
It means the fun starts now.
They are saying the experiment was successful.
Light emission detected.
The spectrum matches that of Quartz.
A Scub has materialized?
Contact team Pied Piper.
How long do we have to be on standby here?
It is an island country, so access by sea is more effective than by air.
We are sitting just outside Japanese territorial waters.
If we move any closer, we will get caught in the net of the Japanese army.
Their patrolling battleships will likely
Just now the Japanese apparently succeeded with their experiment.
If there is a Scub Burst, then a Secret will...
Emergence confirmed.
What just happened?
Emergency alert from the experiment area.
A Secret has been sighted on the sea!
Commence operation to capture the Secret.
Request an area check of the experiment area.
What on Earth...
Secrets have a much higher potential as weapons in real battles than IFOs.
It is all right.
The Secret targets the Scub Coral.
Which means we are safe as long as we are
Damage confirmed in the battleships standing by.
We are under attack by the Secret!
Eh, you will not take the bait?
For this operation, you have been dispatched
to the seabed south of Tokyo Bay near the mouth of the Sagami river.
For most of its area, the Tokyo Bay is around 20 meters deep,
but this area is exceptional in that it reaches as deep as 500 meters.
Taking the water pressure at that depth into consideration,
there is a risk of the IFO's frame suffering damage, primarily the limbs.
To prevent this, all units are advised to stay in flyer form as long as possible,
and only convert to human form when the conditions are fitting.
Which means, do not transform until the very last moment.
That is crazy!
It would be nice if the enemy is kind enough to wait until we complete our transformation sequences.
But then why are we attacking underwater?
We could just go and fight above the water.
Our target this time is not the Secret but the Scub Coral underwater.
Retrieving the Quartz takes top priority.
The Secret is moving towards the JAF base.
We will take that chance to move into where the Scub Coral materialized,
destroy the Scub, retrieve the Quartz, and retreat immediately.
Roger.
What is that Quartz thing?
It is a crystal inside the Scub Coral that the Secrets are targeting.
The Quartz is that thing they had us transport?
Yeah.
The Generation Bleu folks think that the Secrets are going for those.
They are hiding the all the Quartz they have retrieved from the Scub somewhere in the HQ.
Why?
Who knows...
So Generation Bleu's top priority has always been retrieving the Quartz?
This time in particular.
To prevent a dangerous incident with Japan, we must destroy the Scub as well.
And what about rescuing the victims?
If we suppress the Scub Burst by retrieving the Quartz, damages can be kept to a minimum.
Oh, please.
It is pointless to talk back, Ao.
They are the type of people who look away if there is something they do not want to see.
Fighting is heartless.
We cannot allow Japan to emerge as a trapar superpower.
You are Okinawan so you should understand!
What are you talking about?!
I do not care if they are Japanese or Okinawan, people are dying out there!
Stop, Ao!
Alleluia, Kyrie, prioritize retrieving the Quartz.
Understood.
Roger.
Fuck...
Fuck...
We would have been better off if we had just infiltrated their base!
I get that, but do not drive so recklessly!
Cars are so last century!
If there is an explosion in the military harbor, that means the Secret is in the water over there!
Hey, is not that...
our Mark I?!
What is wrong?!
Why did you stop?
That is my Nirvash.
Who are you?
Thank you for using my present so well.
You are a member of the Fire Cracker?
My name is Truth.
You are that guy from the toilet...
Is this mess all your doing?
This... is not a Scub Coral!
Damaged Quartz...
Why is there so much?
And this light...
It is been reactivated.
Damaged Quartz is a side product of a Scub Burst.
Look at how much there is left.
Taking all this into consideration with other data...
It is the remains from the Scub Burst 70 years ago.
If you gather enough damaged Quartz in one spot, it is going to go bang again.
I guessed a Secret would show up then.
And I was right.
Fake Quartz?
Then that time...
Where is it?
Dammit!
This is bad!
The pressure will crush Nirvash!
Where is it?
Where is the Secret?
At least call for help!
Fleur?
Fleur!
What is it doing?
That is...
I see!
What are you doing?!
Ao, what was that for?!
Come!
No way...
Tell me this is not happening...
But...
Huh?
I thought you were not going to help him if he was going to drown.
Shut up!
Answer me!
Were you the one who gave us that?
You cannot see the truth.
What did you say?
The truth only shows itself to the ones who try to see it.
Hey, how did you know that the Secret was going for the trapar?
I saw it.
Saw what?
Something we cannot see?
Is that your special ability?
Like clairvoyance?
I do not know...
I just saw it when I tried to...
That is all I can say.
I hope you can understand now.
Japan needs no overwhelming military power.
Even meager peace is better than none.
You...
What do you want?
You got in my way!
You said you want to destroy this country.
Would you really be satisfied with just destroying this tiny nation?
To be continued!
Next time on Eureka Seven AO.
In the land of the great power America, mankind's choice triggers
a fearful evolution in the Secrets, fueled by the sacrifice Truth prepared.
Can Ao's team overcome this difficult situation and resolve the crisis?
Eureka Seven AO, episode ten: Release Yourself.
Listen to the voices of the children of the stars.
In The Dark We Live
Sign: Revised budget estimates for pseudo Scub Burst simulations
